        "content": "from datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(title=\"Software Engineer\", dept=\"\", loc=\"Remote\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n                url=\"u\", department=dept, location=loc, posted_at=posted_at)\n\ndef test_exclude_wins_over_include_on_same_match():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Manager\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"manager\"], exclude=[\"manager\"]) is False\n\ndef test_include_word_boundary_no_partial_match():\n    j = _job(title=\"Engineering Manager\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"eng\"]) is False  # \"eng\" != whole word\n\ndef test_location_is_case_insensitive_substring():\n    j = _job(loc=\"San Francisco, CA\")\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_drops_confirmed_old_job():\n    old = _job(posted_at=\"2020-01-01T00:00:00Z\")\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n    assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\ndef test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at():\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"garbage\")\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True  # can't confirm it's old -> keep\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_converts_to_cutoff():\n    old = _job(posted_at=\"2000-01-01T00:00:00Z\")\n    fresh = _job(title=\"X\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    out = filter_jobs([old, fresh], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n    assert out == [fresh]\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_empty_rules_returns_all():\n    jobs = [_job(), _job(title=\"Other\")]\n    assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n",
