        "content": "\n**Gaps (each notifier has an untested no-op guard AND an untested send path):**\n- `notify_slack`/`notify_webhook`/`notify_email`/`notify_sms`: no-op when env var(s) unset; no-op when `new`/`changed` both empty even if configured; correct payload shape when configured.\n- `notify_sms`: partial env vars (3 of 4 set) still no-ops; `resp.raise_for_status()` propagates on Twilio error (e.g. bad creds) — this exception is what `dispatch` is relied on to catch.\n- `_sms_body`: truncates at `limit`, \"+N more\" line, ASCII-only (no `•`/`…`).\n- `dispatch`: **critical gap** — a failing notifier (e.g. Slack webhook down) must not prevent later notifiers (SMS, email) from running. This is the entire reason `dispatch` wraps each call in try/except but it's never verified.\n\n```python\n",
