        "title": "6. `fetchers.py` — largest surface, currently **zero coverage** on 15 ATS parsers + pagination + retry",
        "content": "\nThis module is explicitly designed to be testable (\"client is injectable... unit-testable against mocked transports\") — but nothing exercises that design.\n\n**A. Retry/backoff (`_request`) — highest priority, this is shared infra for every fetcher:**\n- 200 on first try (no retry).\n- 500 then 200 → succeeds after retry (use `respx` or a fake transport, and monkeypatch `asyncio.sleep` to avoid real delays).\n- 429 exhausts all `retries` → raises `RuntimeError`.\n- non-retryable 4xx (e.g. 404) raises immediately without retrying.\n- `httpx.TransportError` (connection reset) retried same as 5xx.\n\n```python\n",
