        "title": "tests/test_fetchers_request.py",
        "content": "import httpx, pytest\nimport fetchers\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_retries_on_500_then_succeeds(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fetchers.asyncio, \"sleep\", lambda *_: None)\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 2:\n            return httpx.Response(500)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []})\n    transport = httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport) as client:\n        r = await fetchers._request(client, \"https://x/jobs\")\n        assert r.status_code == 200 and calls[\"n\"] == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_exhausts_retries_raises_runtimeerror(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(fetchers.asyncio, \"sleep\", lambda *_: None)\n    transport = httpx.MockTransport(lambda r: httpx.Response(429))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await fetchers._request(client, \"https://x/jobs\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_404_raises_without_retry(monkeypatch):\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    transport = httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await fetchers._request(client, \"https://x/jobs\", retries=3)\n        assert calls[\"n\"] == 1  # no retry on non-retryable status\n```\n\n**B. Parsers — pure functions, trivially unit-testable with fixture payloads, currently 0 of 15 covered:**\n\nEach of `parse_greenhouse`, `parse_lever` (+`_lever_salary`), `parse_ashby` (+`_ashby_salary`, `isListed=False` filter), `parse_smartrecruiters`, `parse_recruitee` (flat-string vs city/country-assembled location), `parse_workable` (dict-location vs flat-location branches), `parse_google` (+`_extract_ds1` regex, +`_ds1_posted_at` index fallback 12→13→14), `parse_deshaw` (regex-card dedup via `seen`), `parse_twosigma` (3x-render dedup, bounded location lookahead), `parse_optiver` (external_id slug derivation), `parse_microsoft`, `parse_netflix` (comma-packed location respacing), `parse_amazon` (+`_amazon_posted_at` valid/malformed).\n\n```python\n",
