        "content": "\n**Gaps:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run window (`since_days`) applied when no marker; existing marker used instead; **group-boundary truncation** at `limit` (never splits a `first_seen` group — worth a test where a group of 3 rows sharing one timestamp straddles the limit) and `watermark` reflects the last *complete* group, not a partial one.\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now`; valid explicit watermark; invalid ISO string → returns `2` and doesn't call `set_meta`; neither arg → returns `2`.\n- `_normalize_ats`: each of the 14 char-replacement rules; replacements skipped inside `<style>`/`<script>` and inside tag attributes (only body text, per the comment at agent.py:181-184) — the split-on-tags logic is subtle and untested.\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file → returns `2`; output not starting with `%PDF` → returns `1` and prints stderr tail (mock `subprocess.run`).\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env override when path exists; `shutil.which` discovery; macOS app-bundle fallback; `sys.exit` when nothing found.\n- `main()` argv routing: bare invocation → interactive; `scan` → headless; `-i` flag anywhere → forces interactive; flag splitting between mode words and passthrough `extra` args.\n\n```python\n",
